    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-03T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-03T23:00:00-05:00" n="156"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 G 231/582: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-04T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 4, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1430. In a friendly private conversation with me yesterday afternoon Foreign
                    Minister Soong on his own initiative referred to an article regarding me in
                    Washington Merry-Go-Round of October 28,<note n="50" xml:id="d156fn50">Drew
                        Pearson had reported that it was an inescapable fact that Generalissimo
                        Chiang Kai-shek did not like Ambassador Gauss and would like to have him
                        replaced.</note> which he described as “clumsy propaganda” and said that the
                    article had come to the notice of the Generalissimo who had desired Soong to
                    tell me that the statements in the article regarding Chiang’s attitude toward me
                    were entirely untrue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
